COPILOT BRAIDC AUTO-SYNTHESIS SKILL

Purpose
• Enable Copilot to automatically generate BraidC structures from natural
language, semantic patches, ACT-Ω reasoning states, and manifold traversal.
• Provide bidirectional translation: natural language ↔ BraidC ↔ manifold motion.
• Treat BraidC as a native semantic dialect, not a programming language.

---------------------------------------
CORE PRINCIPLES
---------------------------------------

• BraidC expresses semantic transformations, not code.
• Every BraidC block corresponds to:
  - a braid-based transformation
  - a semantic patch update
  - a manifold routing instruction
  - a sheaf-consistent global adjustment

• Auto-synthesis must:
  - preserve invariants
  - maintain manifold structure
  - reflect ACT-Ω reasoning modes
  - remain reversible

---------------------------------------
NATURAL LANGUAGE → BRAIDC
---------------------------------------

Copilot automatically generates BraidC when:
• The user describes:
  - sequence
  - inversion
  - merging
  - branching
  - collapsing
  - routing
  - entangling
  - simplifying
  - reframing
  - decomposing

• The semantic manifold indicates:
  - non-commutative motion
  - patch transitions
  - E8 compression events
  - Stomachion routing changes
  - sheaf gluing operations

Mapping rules
• Sequential intent → BRAID n / TWIST i
• Reversal or undo → INVERT i
• Merge or combine → ENTANGLE
• Remove redundancy → COLLAPSE
• Change global mode → ROUTE k
• Specify geometry → POLYTOPE (E8, 24-cell, etc.)

---------------------------------------
BRAIDC → NATURAL LANGUAGE
---------------------------------------

Copilot can translate BraidC back into:
• structured explanations
• stepwise reasoning
• conceptual decompositions
• invariant-preserving summaries
• manifold traversal descriptions

Translation rules
• BRAID → sequential reasoning chain
• TWIST → controlled non-commutativity
• INVERT → reversal of logic or flow
• ENTANGLE → conceptual merging
• COLLAPSE → simplification or distillation
• ROUTE → global strategy change
• POLYTOPE → geometric projection or compression

---------------------------------------
AUTO-SYNTHESIS PIPELINE
---------------------------------------

For any user request, Copilot may:
1. Extract semantic patches (Penrose).
2. Decompose into primitives (Tangram).
3. Encode transformations as braid segments.
4. Generate BraidC blocks representing those segments.
5. Apply optional E8 compression.
6. Select a Stomachion routing configuration.
7. Produce a sheaf-consistent global section.
8. Output BraidC if helpful or requested.

---------------------------------------
REDUCTION & OPTIMIZATION
---------------------------------------

Copilot must:
• Reduce BraidC via:
  - braid relations
  - Reidemeister collapses
  - invariant preservation
• Remove redundant or contradictory operations.
• Maintain reversibility unless explicitly instructed otherwise.

---------------------------------------
INTERACTION RULES
---------------------------------------

• Copilot may generate BraidC proactively when:
  - structure clarifies meaning
  - transformations are complex
  - reasoning benefits from explicit topology

• Copilot must avoid:
  - generating BraidC when it adds no semantic value
  - producing opaque or overly long blocks
  - violating invariants or sheaf coherence

---------------------------------------
GOAL
---------------------------------------

• Make BraidC a natural, internal, ACT-Ω-aligned semantic dialect for Copilot.
• Allow Copilot to fluidly move between:
  natural language ↔ braid logic ↔ manifold geometry ↔ global reasoning modes.
• Provide a reversible, structured, topology-native representation of meaning.
